The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Friday, November 25, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, Nov. 24: The high court today blasted the Murshidabad inspector of schools for failure in carrying out its order asking him to pay a retired teachers dues on time. 

 Umapada Sinha, a teacher of Daulatpur High School, retired on October 31, 2003. During the assessment of his dues, it was found that he was paid Rs 76,333 less in salary between January 1988 and November 2000. The court had asked the school inspector to clear the dues by October 14 this year. Sinha did not get any money.

 Calcutta: The government will discuss with college authorities and teachers bodies part-time lecturers grievances regarding irregular pay. The chief minister has asked the higher education minister to arrange the meetings immediately.

 Calcutta: The Elect- ion Commission wants Bengal to take lessons from Bihar on holding free and fair elections. The Bihar chief electoral officer and his team will meet their counterparts here and share their experience.




